RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 59. Claiming Purse 18500. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS SIRED BY REGISTERED INDIANA STALLIONS FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since August 21 Allowed 2 l bs. Claiming Price $15,000 (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHEZA NUT took control shortly away from the gates, set a well measured, well rated pace on a clear lead, widened her advantage turning for home and kept on unchallenged to the wire. BICARB BETTY tracked the pace to the far turn, rallied up two wide to be prominent at the head of the lane and finished well while no match for the winner. MEAN ELENITA stalked the pace while well positioned along the rail, rallied turning for home while cutting the corner and lacked a late response. EMPIRE SUNRISE chased the early pace through the first turn, dropped back down the backside to trail and passed weaker down the lane. TRIP CHARGE raced four wide down the backside while moving up to be prominently placed and faded in the far turn. QUITE WHIMSICAL rushed up between horses down the backstretch to make an early bid and gave way turning for home.

ENTRY.NAME: Bicarb Betty
ENTRY.OWNER: Clabar Mor Stables LLC and Haran Thoroughbreds LLC
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked pace, bid, no match, second best

ENTRY.NAME: Mean Elenita
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace, inside, lacked late response

ENTRY.NAME: Sheza Nut
ENTRY.COMMENT: took control, well rated, clear lead, unchallenged

MANUELITO raced along the fence from off the pace down the backstretch, crept up the rail through the turn while steadily making up ground, cut the corner turning for home and finished well along the fence to gain the place. FIRST CROWNED broke alertly to take the lead from the gate, dueled from two wide to deep stretch and weakened inside the final hundred yards in a game effort. CIBOLO raced close up for the first quarter, lost position in the turn and came again belatedly to be gaining at the wire. HARD LUCK JUSTICE was never a factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOODBETTERBEST sped to the lead into the first turn, opened a wide advantage down the backstretch, weakened turning for home and held on late. TIZ ERIN stalked the pacesetter from afar, narrowed the margin through the turn while saving ground along the fence and kept grinding down the lane to gain the place. FLURR raced mid-pack along the rail down the backside, waited behind rivals through the turn and made a mild bid down the lane. CALM COOL made no impact and raced very wide down the lane. SWIGERT well placed to challenge midway on the final bend and weakened turning for home. MISS DIAMOND RICH was never a threat. DEE DEE B dropped back through the field down the backside and was not a factor.
